==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dukhobortsy
<hw>Du*kho*bor"tsy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Russ.
<ets>dukhobortsy</ets> spirit wrestlers; <ets>dukh</ets> spirit +
<ets>bortsy</ets> wrestlers.]</ety> <def>A Russian religious sect
founded about the middle of the 18th century at Kharkov. They believe
that Christ was wholly human, but that his soul reappears from time to
time in mortals. They accept the Ten Commandments and the
⟦ldquo⟧useful⟦rdquo⟧ portions of the Bible, but deny the need of rulers,
priests, or churches, and have no confessions, icons, or marriage
ceremonies. They are communistic, opposed to any violence, and unwilling
to use the labor of animals. Driven out of Russia proper, many have
emigrated to Cyprus and Canada. See <er>Raskolnik</er>, below.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dulcamara</ent>⟦br⟧
